@node "Förord" "Förord"


                                  PREFACE

    I abnegiate all responsibility on damages from Lexikon, despite of
    careful testing. This program may be freely copied with condition
    that no files is changed, deleted or added. You may also never
    take more charge than the cost for diskscopy etc.
@endnode

@node "Intro" "Introduktion"


                               INTRODUCTION

    SHORT LIST OF FEATURES

    - Search for the translation of both english and swedish words.
    - Write your own translations.                  (registred only).
    - Count the number of words in your database.
    - Sort the words in your listwindow.
    - Use speech with translator.library.
    - Ikonify the titelbar.
    - Jump through public screens.
    - @{"Arexx" link "Arexx" 0}-support             (registred only).
    - Sensitive for the screenfont.
    - Online help with AmigaGuide.
    - Windowpositions etc. can be saved.            (registred only).
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"


                               INSTALLATION

    This is done with the installer-script.
    OBS. Lexikon reguire Kickstart 2.0 to work!

    OBS. If no directory is given for your database
    LEXIKON:Words is searched.
@endnode

@node "VK" "Verktygstyper"

    Lexikon take argument from both Shell and WorkBench.
    They work after the same template:

    DIR=DIRECTORY/K/A,HELPDIR/K,ZOOM/S,XA/K,YA/K,XB/K,YB/K,
      LISTWIDTH/K,LISTHEIGHT/K,PORTNAME/K,NOSORT/S,
      NOACTIVATE/S,NOAREXX/S,FRONTMOST/S,SWEDGAD/S

    DIRECTORY - A directory that contains the directory Words.
              This stores all files for the database.
              Must exist if ont the volume LEXIKON: exists.
              Ex DIRECTORY DH2:
              Then Lexikon search in the directory DH2:Words/ that contains
              the database.

    HELPDIR - Give an alternative directory for the helpfile Lexikon.guide.

    ZOOM    - Give that the window is started in zoomed location.
              Ex ZOOM

    XA      - X-pos for the upper left corner of the mainwindow.
              Ex XA=100

    YA      - Y-pos for the upper left corner of the mainwindow.
              Ex YA=100

    XB      - X-pos for the upper left corner of the listwindow.
              Ex XB=50

    YB      - Y-pos for the upper left corner of the listwindow.
              Ex YB=200

    LISTWIDTH - Width of the listwindows

    LISTHEIGHT - Height of listwindow.

    PORTNAME - Name for the Arexxport.
              Ex PORTNAME=Foobar

    NOSORT  - The items in the listwindow is not sorted when they are read.
              Ex NOSORT

    NOACTIVATE - The stringgadget is not activated when you have searched for
              a word.
              Ex NOACTIVATE

    NOAREXX - The Arexxport will not open. You save little  memory, and you
              don't need to have libs:rexxhost.library.
              Ex NOAREXX

    FRONTMOST - The window will open on the frontmost public screen.
              If the screen is private it will open on Workbench as usual.

    SWEDGAD - The Swedish stringgadget will be activated at start.

    See preferences then they have higher priority than tooltypes.
@endnode

@node "AV" "Användning"


                                USAGE

    Before use Lexikon must be @{"installed." link "Install" 0}

    This is the program who may do the life a bit easier for you who have
    to use the English-Swedish Dictionary often. A computer is as you know
    faster than human in many areas, and because of this, searching for
    words is an excellent job.

    Press the HELP-key in Lexikon to load this helptext.
    (Only Kickstart 3.0 or higher). Do you think that the helpwindow
    has wrong size choose the menu "Settings/Save As Defaults".
        

    SEARCH FOR WORDS

    If you write 'cat' in the box for english words a listwindow will
    appear that show all english words that start with these
    characters. You don't need to write the whole word. The
    listwindows titelbar show how many "hits" there was. You have a
    scrollbar to the right. The program sense in which gadget you
    wrote and show the proper translation.

    @{"Menus" link "MY" 0}

    @{"Gadgets" link "KP" 0}
@endnode

@node "MY" "Menyer"


                                  MENUS

    Lexikon/Information

        Some general information about Lexikon.
        @{"The programmer" link "Slut" 0}.
        Is Lexikon @{"registred" link "Reg" 0}.
        Time and date for the compilation.
        Screenname that Lexikon use.
        Name at Lexikons @{"Arexxport" link "Arexx" 0} (registred only).


    Lexikon/Help

        Start online help if you have Kickstart 3.0 or higher.

    Lexikon/Quit

        Quit Lexikon.

    Addition/Next screen

        Jump to next public screen if that exists. Could be useful
        wordprocessing etc.

    Preferences/Sort words

        If this item is marked the words are sorted in the listwindow.

    Preferences/Activate string

        If this item is marked, you don't have to press the mousebutton in
        the stringgadget every time a new word is done.

    Preferences/Delete string

        If this item is marked, the string is automatically deleted in the
        stringgadget (the same as RightAmiga - x). Press Arrow UP to get
        the word back.

    Preferences/Save preferences (registred only)

        Saves the configurationen. This contains the following:
        Revision of Lexikon.
        The mainwindows position.
        The listwindows position and size.
        Number of word in the database as seen in the mainwindow.
        The menus Sort words, Aktivera state.
        The gadget Handle in the mainwindow.

        The file Lexikon.cfg is automatically loaded next time the program
        start. Lexikon won't load it if the revision is wrong, you may
        have to save preferences to coreect this.

        Certain things is both saved as @{"tooltypes" link "VK" 0} and
        in preferences. The preferences has higher priority than
        arguments at start.
@endnode

@node "KP" "Knappar"


                                  GADGETS

    Handle:    Search translation/Save translation. (Registred only).
        

    If you want to write new translations, press "Search translation" that
    changes to "Save translation". The program doesn't save until you write
    2 words.

    Every time you store new words the program check the wordlist to see if
    it's already stored. If they exist a requester appear telling you so and
    the words aren't saved. If one of the words already exist, all
    translations are listed. Then choose to save the new one or not.


    Save

    You can save the contents in the listwindow in a ususal textfile.
    If it exists, choose between add or write over it.


    Print

    You can print out all words in the listwindow to the printer. A window
    appear with a button to cancel the printout, but the printer contain
    a buffer so the printout may not stop immediately.


    Talk

    If you have written a word in a box and press Talk then it says
    the word. Due to a strange bug in narrator.device (I think)
    you have to press this 2 times to make it work. Unfortunately
    the files devs:narrator.device and libs:translator.library disappear
    when WB2.1 came. But if you have WB2.0 or WB1.3 just copy them to their
    places.


    Count

    You can count all words in the wordlist. Every translation is
    counted as 2 words.


                                Listwindow

    Here is the result of the search in the wordlist. Can also be used to
    show synonyms when you save.
@endnode

@node "Arexx" "Arexx"


                              AREXX
    _________________________________________________________
   |                                                         |
   | OBS Lexikon must be registred to make Arexx to work !!! |
   |_________________________________________________________|

    Theese Arexx-scripts is in the registred verion.
    These can be used to connect CygnusEd with Lexikon.
    The Installer-script copies these to REXX: if you don't choose
    another directory.

    Translate.ced - Translates occcasional words in Ced.

    1. Start Arexx with RexxMast if it is not running.
    2. Start Lexikon.
    3. Start CygnusEd.
    4. Put the cursor on a English or Swedish word in Ced depending what
       language is active in Lexikon.
    5. Write 'Rx translate.ced' in Shell or attach it to a key in Ced.
    6. A list of words is now shown on Ced's screen.


    Translate_Eng.ced - The same script as Translate.ced but always
    translates English to Swedish.


    Translate_Sve.ced - The same script as Translate.ced but always
    translates Swedish to English.


    Add.ced - Importers *.gls-files from Glosförhör by Stefan Petterson

    1. Start Arexx with RexxMast if it is not running.
    2. Start Lexikon.
    3. Start CygnusEd.
    4. Load a gls-file in that view.
    5. Write 'Rx add.lex' in Shell or attach it to a key in Ced..
    6. Lexikon now importers the words FROM the *.gls-file to its wordlist.
       Checking for duplicates is done.


    Include.ced - Updates a wordlist from another wordlist.

    1. Start Arexx with RexxMast if it is not running.
    2. Start Lexikon.
    3. Create the directory Words in Ram:
    4. Copy the wordlist (Lex#?-files) to the new catalog.
       Lexikon will update the ordinary wordlist from RAM:words/
    5. Write 'Rx include.lex' in Shell.


                 TO WRITE OWN AREXXPROGRAMS IN AREXX

    You must write "address 'Lexikon1'" in the Arexx-programs beginning to
    control Lexikon. Write "options result" to see the returnkod.

    It doesn't matter if  you have uppercase or lowercase in your commands.
    When you do a search in the wordlist you get a ACTUAL WORDLIST
    in return that I refer to below.

        Observ that you include '' if = exists in your command.
        SAVEWORDS LAN=English doesn't work but
        'SAVEWORDS LAN=English' do.

    Is there wrong syntax Lexikon will return code 5. The variable RESULT
    often contain some type of information from an Arexx-command.
    When you search for a word you get one or more hits in the wordlist.
    These are collected in a ACTUAL WORDLIST that I refer to below.

    Observe that it may be good to use marks in leery cases.
    If the commands contain swedish characters 'ĺäö' '=' etc.

    SEARCH         WORD,LAN=LANGUAGE/K/A,STEM/K,QUIET/S,EXACT/S,STRIP/S
                   Search for a word in the wordlist.

        WORD     - Word to search.
        LANGUAGE - Choose language. Ex: English, Swedish.
        STEM     - An Arexx-variable to store the actual wordlist.
                   Ex.    SEARCH WORD=sunsh STEM=mylist
                   mylista.1 now contains sunshade = solparasoll
                   mylista.2 now contains sunshine = solsken
        QUIET    - The listwindow will not open.
        EXACT    - Only those words who exactly correspond with the search
                   is counted as a hit.

        STRIP    - You get only the words. The example above is then:
                   solparasoll
                   solsken

        The number of "hits" in Result.
        Will return -1 in Result if this fail.
        

-   SAVEWORDS      WORD/M/A,LAN=LANGUAGE/K/A,FORCE/S,CANCEL/S
                   Save a new translation.

        WORD     - 2 strings is feeded here.
                   First the word from the language to translate from
                   then the word to the language to translete to.
                   Ex. from Swedish to English SAVEWORDS sol sun.

        LANGUAGE - Denote what language the first word have.
                   Ex: English, Swedish.

        FORCE    - Save even if ONE (no both) of the words is already in
                   the wordlist.

        CANCEL   - Don't save if ONE of the words is in the wordlist.

        If you give no argument a requester is shown.
        Will return 0 if this fail.


-   SAVE         FILE/K,ADD/S,WRITEOVER/S
                 Save the contents of the listwindow in a file.

        FILE     - filename.
        ADD      - Add the contents to a existing file.
        WRITEOVER - Delete an existing file,
        If no argument a requester is shown.

        Will return the number of words in Result.
        Will return -1 if this fail.


-   PRINT
        Print the contents of the listwindow.

        Will return -1 in Result if this fail.


-   SET         HANDLE/K
                Change variables in Lexikon.

        HANDLE   - Which mode to use. Ex. HANDLE=Save.


-   STATUS      COUNT/S,LANGUAGE/S,HANDLE/S,LIST/S
                Will return information in Result.

        COUNT    - The number of words in the wordlist.
        LANGUAGE - What language to translate from.
                   First language (English default) translate from.
                   Second language (Swedish default)
        HANDLE   - What mode is present.
                   Searchmode.
                   Savemode.
        LIST     - How many words that was counted as "hit" in the latest
                   search.


-   COUNT
        Calculate the number of words in the wordlist.

        Will return the number in Result.
        Will return -1 in Result if this fails.

-   TALK
        Send the text in the stringgadget to the speech (narrator.device).

        Will return -1 in Result if this fails.

-    LOCKGUI
        The user can't use Lexikon.
        The whole control is by Arexx.

-    UNLOCKGUI
        The user can use Lexikon.

-   NEXTSCREEN
        Jump to the next screen.

        Will return -1 in Result if this fails.

-   WINDOW        NAME/K/A,ON/S,OFF/S
        Open or close a window.

        NAME     - Main The main window
                   List The listwindow.

        ON       - Turn on the window.
        OFF      - Turn off the window.

        Will return -1 in Result if this fails.

-   QUIT
        Quit Lexikon

-   VERSION
        Will return the version of Lexikon in Result.
@endnode

@node "Tips" "Lite Tips"


                                ADVICE

    One advice is to get a very useful program called ToolManager2.1.
    You find it on Aminet at:

    ToolManager21b.lha util/boot  490K 163+ToolManager 2.1
    (Binaries and Documentation)

    When this is installed you always have Lexikon on a hotkey, icon
    or a WB-menu.

    If you want to run and release Lexikon from Shell write:
    run <nil: >nil: Lexikon.

    Another smart way is to make an alias in S:Shell-Startup.
    Write : alias run run <nil: >nil:.

    Now it's enough to write "run Lexikon" in a Shell and the close the
    Shell-window. If you don't release it from the Shell Ctrl-C will
    work to quit Lexikon.
@endnode

@node "Teknik" "Teknisk beskrivning"
                            TECHNICAL DESCRIPTION 

    The algoritm for Lexikon to search a word is simple.
    Look for the first character in the searched word, then load the right
    fil and search for the word in that. Example write ca for English
    and the program search in the file LEXc. If I search in Swedish instead
    the file LEXEc is used. This means that all words are stored 2 times
    but in reverse order.

    This is an advantage... The advantage is that you get fast respons
    from the search. If you want to delete a word you have to edit by hand.
    If you want to remove KATT = CAT open LEXEK and LEXc and remove it. 
    Then decrease the number at the files start by one.

    This tells how many translations the file contain. If a word begins at
    Ĺ,Ä or Ö this doesn't work on some filesystem like OFS and FFS.
    International FFS will work. My workaround is to store these in
    LEXE1, LEXE2 and LEXE3.
@endnode

@node "Historia" "Historia"

                                 HISTORIA

Version:

1.0     First working version.

1.01    The words can now contain č , - , ' , ´ , ` .

1.02    Approval now even . and , in the words.

1.03    The program release itself from CLI. Iconify.
        Small bug in the gadgethandling fixed.
        Optimize a bit.

1.04    It starts to get nice!
        Mutual exclusion with formating-gadgets now looks okay.
        You don't have to read the words from disk when the
        formating-gadget is used.
        The tables exchange itself when Swedish/English is choosen and
        the listwindow is opened.
        Internal changes.
        The countwindow remember the position if it closed.

1.10    Now require WB2.0. (Hot advice: get it, it's worth it!)
        The contents in the listwindow can now be saved as a textfile.
        Adjust the topborder after choosen font in WB.
        The kompilationdate is shown in the menu.
        The program can now say the word you wrote.
        The searchroutine is rewritten in assembler.

1.15    A very optimized assembler routine made a guru on a 68000, fixed...
        Thanks Göran Nass for this bugreport.
        The program is now compiled with SAS/C 6.0.

1.16    Compiled with SAS/C 6.1.
        Discovered that SAS has changed some global variables so the name
        Lexikon disappear from the tasklist.
        Soem enforcerhits fixed.
        The iconifywindow is now adjusted for the font.
        Found a logical error when a check for synonyms in the wordlist.

1.20    Compiled with SAS/C 6.2.
        Now uses SystemRequests for messages.
        The Listwindow can now change size and is READONLY.
        Open a requester when the kickstart is below V37.
        Assign is changed from FD.LEXIKON: to LEXIKON:
        can now take a directory instead of assign in Shell.

1.21    A bugfix in the wordsearch...

1.22    Take a directory as argument both from Shell and Workbench
        (tooltypes). Else LEXIKON: is choosen.

1.25    Compiled with SAS/C V6.3.
        The program can now jump to next public screen.
        The number of words is now shown in the main window.
        Some enforcer-hits fixed.

1.27    Can denote a directory several levels down for the wordlist.
        Ex DH0:1/2/3.

1.28    Search for the directory words in Lexikons current directory.
        Compiled with #PRAGMA and saved 2180 bytes.
        The word is now sorted in the listwindow.

1.29    Menuitem to not sort the words in the listwindow. They are shown
        in the order they are sored on the disk.

1.29a   Forgot to call FreeDiskObject() on a place... Fixat.

1.30    All text and all gadgets uses the screens font.
        I used Tim Astons routines in GadLayout from Fish 911.
        Now uses GT_Underscore, hotkey for gadgets.
        Added Quit in the menu.
        Can now quit with Ctrl-C from Shell, doesn't release from Shell.
        Show information about Arexxport and screen in Information.
        Bug in saving of new words, no requester even if one word is
        saved, fixed.
        Lexikon can be controlled by Arexx. Require rexxhost.library.
        Don't require Lexikon.info längre. Can manage a change of name.
        Have discovered a new option in SAS/C OptGlobal. The size
        decreased about 1 kb.
        I thought Optimize was enough...
        Enforcer-hits when saving text is finally fixed. 
        Use NewLook on the menus (only 3.0 or more).
        The progam now contains a versionstring that increase for each
        kompilation.

1.31    Bug when no tooltype for directory is used, fixed.
        Option for start Lexikon iconified.

1.32    Arexx will now work with  ReadArgs().
        Made a unregistred version of Lexikon.
        2 new tooltypes NOSORT and NOACTIVATE.
        Samll fixes.

1.33    Fixed abug that gave guru at certain Arexx sequences.
        New tooltype NOAREXX.

1.34    Online help with Amigaguide (only 3.0 or more).

1.35    Saved 1380 bytes with linking sprintf from amiga.lib.

1.36    Some bugfixes. Hopefully it now works with 2.0.

1.37    2 new tooltypes. LISTWIDTH and LISTHEIGHT.
        Listwindow can now be of any size.

1.38    The preferences can be saved by a menuitem.
        The contents of listwindow is always centered.
        The searchroutine is changed to C because it was too complicated to
        change asm :-).
        1 byte more allocated for the stringbuffer.

1.39    Risk for overwriting memory in the Arexx-function, fixed.

1.40    Compiled with SAS/C 6.55. Saved over 1000 bytes.

1.41    Removed the Languag-gadget. It can sense this anyway.

1.42    Added CR at printing.
        Read Preferences for the printer.

1.43    Increased the stringbuffer from 26 to 70 characters.
        When saving all synonyms is shown after the first word.
        Somewhat faster counting of words with Examine() and ExNext().

1.44    New option FRONTMOST denote that the window will appear on the
        frontscreen if it is public.
        Compiled with SAS/C 6.56, saved over 600 bytes.
        Saves the number of words in preferences.

1.45    After Suggestion from frĺn Jari Kanerva the wordlist is no longer
        converted to uppercase.
        New option to activate the Swedish stringgadget.

1.46    SAVEWORDS in Arexx didn't work in 1.45. Fixed.

1.47    Option FRONTMOST should work better now.
        Fixed: That screen that Lexikon is opened on can't be closed if
        Lexikon jumps to the next screen. fixed.

1.48    Support for localestrings.
        Fixed a bug that make it possible for the Arexx-prg include.lex
        to include multiple kopies of the same string.
        Eg. if the string contain characters outside a-z range.
        Support for 'č' and 'é'.
        Long words are shown better in the listwindow.
        New menuchoice "Delete string"
        Fixed bug when it jumped to a screen with a bigger systemfont.
        Spellchecked the wordlist and founded several errors...

1.49    Error in the menuhandling in the unregistred version.
@endnode

@node "Framtiden" "Framtiden"
                                 THE FUTURE

    I have some plans how to enhance Lexikon. It's just a question
    about time and inspiration...

    Nicer reuesters.
    Possibility to use wildcards.
    A requester for speech adjustment.
    A face with animated mouth that is synchroniced with the talk. Low
    priority but nice anyway :-)
    A function for training your vocabulary.
    Better check if the printer is ok, how?

    Etc. the ideas never ends...

    If you have registred Lexikon you may send me a empty disk in a
    prepaid envelope or email me. I will the send you the latest
    version of Lexikon back.
@endnode

@node "Reg" "Registrering"
                                 SHAREWARE

    I have choosen to publish Lexikon as Shareware. If you register you
    encourage further improvement and get upgrades for free.
    The registred version have this advantages:

    1. You can save your own translations.

    2. Can be controled from Arexx..

    3. An optimized version is compiled for your CPU.
       If you have a 68020 or better the program may go faster

    4. All preferences can be saved by a menuitem.

    Send me 100 SEK or $15 to postal giro 413 15 33-4.
    Or send the money in an envelope if you prefer that.
    On your own risk of course.
@endnode

